ors can attribute their first feature film, or on-screen debut to working with Wallace; from Bryan Brown to Russell Crowe, Naomi Watts and many others.\n\nOver the course of his career, Wallace's films have been recognised with over 38 nominations at local and international film festivals. In 2005, Wallace was awarded an Order of Australia in the Queen's Birthday Honours List for his contributions to the Australian film and television industry as both a director, and to the Australian Screen Directors' Association. In 2012, the ADG awarded Wallace the prestigious Cecil Holmes Award, presented in recognition of advocacy for, and services to directing.\n\nA founding signatory, Wallace was President of the Australian Directors Guild between 1991 and 2000 and remains on the Board today as Treasurer. He currently sits as Chair of The Australian Screen Directors Collecting Society (ASDACS). Source: Wikidata; 01/08/2023", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-10-01T20:39:22.052363+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5202, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stephen_Wallace"}], "uuid": "4f323804-6d93-47e5-8516-97f317b7ef38", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "29094", "external_references": [{"id": 26077, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q7610796"}, {"id": 31631, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "18879145"}, {"id": 31632, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n92078482"}, {"id": 31633, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n92078482"}], "date_modified": "2025-10-01T20:39:22.052644+10:00"}, {"id": 19786, "name": "Don Catchlove", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2130053, "title": "Captives of care", "work_id": 76551, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2130063, "title": "Captives of care", "work_id": 76551, "role": "script", "role_id": 962, "is_primary": false